restaurant.name: Belmora Pizza & Restaurant
restaurant.description: New York pizzeria that offers more than just a plain slice. Generous portion sizes and great hours to always satisfy your pizza needs.

restaurant.name: Marrakesh
restaurant.description: Marrakesh offers a variety of Middle Eastern and Moroccan specialty dishes. The food is delicious, fresh and satisfying.

restaurant.name: Morning Star Cafe
restaurant.description: Favorite Eastside eatery, diner food with fast and reliable service. Endless menu options and large portions.a .30 cents charge for outgoing aluminum containers (as noted on the printed menu)

restaurant.name: Good Nature Deli
restaurant.description: Surprising gem in Midtown East with scrumptious sandwiches and other grill specialties. Food is fresh, delicious and unpretentiously spot on.

restaurant.name: Health King
restaurant.description: Refreshing, thirst-quenching smoothies along with other yummy healthy treats. Energizing brain-food that actually tastes good.In order to process your credit card, Health King requires that you provide your CVV code. The restaurant will be contacting you after you place your order to obtain this information.

restaurant.name: Fresco Tortillas
restaurant.description: Fresco Tortillas is a small food chain that offers big portions of classic Mexican dishes wrapped in freshly made flour tortillas for a reasonable price. Now you can fill up without emptying your wallet!

restaurant.name: East River Cafe
restaurant.description: East River Cafe offers a wide selection of Mediterranean and Italian cuisine- enjoy this fine dining in the comfort of your own home!

restaurant.name: Ginza
restaurant.description: Ginza offers many lunch specials and combination dinners to experience a complete meal of Japanese cuisine from sushi and sashimi to Udon noodles.

restaurant.name: Lasagna Ristorante
restaurant.description: First and only Lasagna restaurant. Italian cuisine that will transport your palate all the way to Italy.

restaurant.name: Cafe Gigi
restaurant.description: Deli fare that is yummy, reasonably priced and perfect for a meal on the go. Salad bar is especially impressive as are the many sandwich and panini choices. Don't forget they serve coffee, slushies and desert.

restaurant.name: Yuva
restaurant.description: Known for it's excellent delivery, Yuva serves Indian delights better than the rest. Indian flavors don't lose their kick and dishes arrive ready for a delicious, indulgent dinner experience.

restaurant.name: Cafe Daniello's
restaurant.description: Classic Italian cuisine that delivers with a punch. Great slices, rave-worthy tomato sauce and other notable dishes as well.

restaurant.name: Liberty Cafe / Taco Bell
restaurant.description: Deli fare with reasonable prices and a taco bell tucked away in the back. Great spot for breakfast and lunch when you want good food and are tired of your usual overpriced egg sandwich.Please note that during lunch time (from 11:00 AM until 1:30 PM) and inclement weather, there may be an additional 30 minute delay added to the expected delivery time of 45 to 50 minutes.

restaurant.name: Luscious Thai
restaurant.description: As its name entails, Luscious Thai serves Thai creations of classic cuisines with beef, chicken, seafood, noodle and rice. Take advantage of their lunch special deals!

restaurant.name: Portofino
restaurant.description: Beyond your average pizza slice, Portofino offers many variety pizza options with delicious and unique toppings. And the prices are hard to beat.

restaurant.name: Oriental Noodle Shop
restaurant.description: Chinese restaurant in midtown east that many claim to be above the plethora of Chinese restaurants found in China Town. The food is flavorful and satisfying with prices a little higher than standard China Town fare.

restaurant.name: Ginger Asian Fusion
restaurant.description: Excellent prices attract many to the menu, but the food is just as enticing. Sushi is always fresh, while there are plenty of other Asian Fusion options for the non-sushi fan.

restaurant.name: Cozy Corner
restaurant.description: Perfect for a quick lunch, Cozy Corner covers all the basics with hot dogs, burgers, salads, and sandwiches. Try a side order of melted cheese fries or stuffed grapes leaves to complete your meal!

restaurant.name: Grill44 NYC
restaurant.description: Small but delicious Indian restaurant. Their quick service and flavorful, spicy food makes this the perfect spot for a fast but yummy meal.

restaurant.name: Grand Sichuan Chinese
restaurant.description: One of NYC's top 100 Chinese restaurants. Sizzling sichuan dishes that only leave you wanting more. A hot-spot and always crowded, delivery service allows you to enjoy the tantalizing flavors without the wait.

restaurant.name: Fusion Grills
restaurant.description: Food court Chinese food in public atrium on Third Avenue. Typical choices but nonetheless tasty.

restaurant.name: Beekman Liquors
restaurant.description: Looking for any kind of wine and chances are Beekman can find it for you. Extensive knowledge of wines and other liquor make Beekman stand above its competitors. Please allow 1 hour for deliveries. Please allow up to 90 minutes for deliveries West of 6th.

restaurant.name: Chin Chin
restaurant.description: Chinese restaurant where the food is just oh-so tasty. Everything is cooked to perfection, oozing with powerful flavors and never too greasy or over salted. The food is fun, creative and overall delicious.

restaurant.name: Little Slice of Italy
restaurant.description: Pizza is far from the main dish at this Italian eatery, with a menu including heros, sandwiches, and pasta dishes. Order your gourmet pizza and more today to taste a little slice of Italy!

restaurant.name: Maharaja Indian Restaurant & Cafe
restaurant.description: Indian food that definitely satisfies the palate with exotic spices and flavor combinations. Prices are very reasonable and the menu has a lot of options including classic favorites like Chicken Tikka Masala.

restaurant.name: Pastafina
restaurant.description: Pizzeria that caters to New Yorkers needs. Pizza is crunchy and hot and the other entree's offer hearty portions and great flavor.

restaurant.name: Pita Grill
restaurant.description: Mediterranean fare in Midtown East. Flavorful chicken dishes with sauces to match.

restaurant.name: Evergreen Shanghai Restaurant
restaurant.description: Chinese restaurant that sometimes gets overlooked but serves delicious food. The menu lists many creative main dishes that leave diners surprised and craving more!

restaurant.name: Krunch Pizza Bar
restaurant.description: "It's hip to eat square," is the motto at this unconventional pizza shop. Krunch only uses the freshest ingredients to create slices beyond the traditional cheese choice.

restaurant.name: Kami Sushi Japanese Cuisine
restaurant.description: Reasonably priced delivery sushi. Ingredients are fresh and the quality is equally impressive.

restaurant.name: Lilli & Loo Asian Cuisine & Sushi Bar
restaurant.description: Lilli and Loo offers an extensive menu of Asian cuisine ranging from fresh sushi to chicken, beef, noodle and tofu entrees. Take advantage of these reasonably priced lunch specials and top it off with a pearl tapioca tea!

restaurant.name: Go Noodle Chinese Restaurant
restaurant.description: Cheap Chinese, loyal taste and lots of noodles. A great low-key noodle joint that's light on the wallet and heavy with great flavors.

restaurant.name: Rustica Trattoria Pizzeria
restaurant.description: Known for their pizza this midtown east restaurant serves all its local New Yorkers the cheesy heaven we all crave. While the pizza stands above the rest don't shy away from the many other Italian classic dishes.

restaurant.name: Bistro 61
restaurant.description: Executive Chef Anthony Raggiri has brought his skills, honed in Marseilles as an apprentice in his father's butcher's shop and also at the prestigious La Cadennelle, to Bistro 61. Get a taste of his classically French cuisine delivered straight to your door tonight!

restaurant.name: Wild Ginger
restaurant.description: Delicious Asian Fusion dishes done with sophistication. Combinations of flavors are fresh and exciting. With so many options on the menu customers can continually sample new dishes that are always great!

restaurant.name: John & Tony's
restaurant.description: John and Tony's is a pizzeria and restaurant that serves Italian classic dishes as well as new, inventive ones such as the Nacho Pizza or the Tuna Fish Pizza. Best of all, John and Tony's is open most nights until at least 4 a.m. so get these eats even late at night!

restaurant.name: Little Thai Kitchen
restaurant.description: Great place to order from when you want to savor delicious Thai dishes at home. Dishes are flavorful, spicy and cooked with care and expertise.

restaurant.name: Tadka
restaurant.description: Delicious Indian restaurant serving all your classic Indian dishes filled with lots of flavor. Service is fast and the food is decently priced.

restaurant.name: Cafe K
restaurant.description: Kosher Italian food that is truly delicious. The many seafood options dominate diners picks but they also have great breakfast which is very satisfying.

restaurant.name: Melita Wines & Liquors
restaurant.description: Great liquor store with a wide variety of merchandise and great customer service. Many products on hand make customers very satisfied with Melita Wine and Liquors.

restaurant.name: Crisp
restaurant.description: Rave worthy Mediterranean restaurant that not only serves the fast growing trend of falafel and hummus but does it right! All the food is expertly prepared, never greasy and oh-so yummy.

restaurant.name: Caffe Martier
restaurant.description: Great little cafe with more than just your morning cup-of-joe including pastries, eggs and lunch food. The little French touches add to the ambiance of this charming spot.

restaurant.name: Brick Lane Curry House
restaurant.description: A small Indian treasure that knows about good food and flavors. Dishes are hot and bursting with flavor. If you think you can handle spicy foods don't be afraid to ask and they will honor your request!

restaurant.name: Ichiro II
restaurant.description: Ichiro II is a sushi restaurant with an extensive array of choices for rolls. Make sure to try a hot or cold appetizer to go along with your sushi or teriyaki meal!

restaurant.name: Parnell's Pub
restaurant.description: A taste of Ireland in NYC. This midtown east pub serves hearty and comforting dishes that will definitely have you planning your trip to Ireland very shortly.

restaurant.name: Sophie's Cuban Cuisine
restaurant.description: Cuban cravings be-gone at this favorite NYC eatery. Satisfying, savory, and delicious are just a few words used to describe Sophie's. Not to mention reasonable prices.

restaurant.name: Chola NY
restaurant.description: Acclaimed as the best Indian restaurant in NYC, ordering any of the Indian dishes from Chola will leave you happy and satisfied. They offer all the classic Indian favorites as well as other dishes many Indian restaurants leave out.

restaurant.name: Yushi
restaurant.description: Delicious Japanese restaurant. Diners love that Yushi provides calorie information for all their food as well as serving only the freshest seafood. Sometimes the prices can run high but the food and quality are worth it.

restaurant.name: Good Health Burgers
restaurant.description: Fresh and flavorful burgers for all! Burgers are all cooked brilliantly and are accompanied by only the best toppings. Plenty of vegetarian options as well.

restaurant.name: Baluchi's
restaurant.description: With many locations all around New York, Baluchi's consistently delivers flavorful North Indian food. While there are plenty of delicious meat options, many vegetarian choices are also available.

restaurant.name: Midtown Diner
restaurant.description: An inexpensive diner with the classics you know and love. Many traditional Greek dishes available as well.

restaurant.name: Ah Chihuahua!
restaurant.description: Great Mexican food at a great price. All your favorite Mexican staples, cooked well and thoroughly enjoyable.

restaurant.name: Baja Fresh
restaurant.description: Yes it is a chain restaurant but that doesn't mean you don't crave quick and easy Mexican food. The prices sometimes run higher than you would like for fast food but sometimes Mexican food can be hard to find and this definitely satisfies the craving.

restaurant.name: Ranch 1
restaurant.description: Everyone needs their fast food pick and Ranch 1 is the place to do it. The meals are good, well-priced and the chicken is delightfully satisfying.

restaurant.name: Benvenuto Grille
restaurant.description: Popular cafe with a very extensive menu. Serving breakfast before 11, the egg options help you start the day off right. For a later treat there are tons of options from pasta and hot entrees to wraps and salads.

restaurant.name: Aja
restaurant.description: Fresh and delicious sushi are not the only option on the menu. Aside from impressive platters of sushi and sashimi, Aja offers other interesting and satisfying food including the steak and deserts.

restaurant.name: Bombay Bistro
restaurant.description: Quality ingredients and the best Indian spices go into making the food served at Bombay Bistro.

restaurant.name: Abitino's Pizza & Italian Kitchen
restaurant.description: New Yorker's are never sick of pizza and Abitino's proves to continually satisfy all pizza lovers. In addition to the variety of slices available, the garlic knots are a hit too!

restaurant.name: Padre Figlio
restaurant.description: An Italian restaurant with an impressive menu that is always pleasing its customers. The portions are a nice size and everything is always cooked to perfection. Main courses are all delicious but don't forget to save room for desert.

restaurant.name: Teresa's Gourmet
restaurant.description: Teresa's Gourmet offers a wide range of delicious breakfast and lunch options. The prices are fairly reasonable compared to other similar spots in the neighborhood. The food is always fresh and the meat is hearty and yummy.

restaurant.name: Keats Restaurant
restaurant.description: While Keats is a fun bar and awesome Karaoke spot on Saturday nights, the food is also something to talk about. Everything is cooked well, seasoned nicely and leaves you satisfied. They don't serve frozen meats that are re-heated, everything is down right fresh.

restaurant.name: Thai 51
restaurant.description: Absolutely delicious Thai food that is presented beautifully and tastes just as good. The restaurant itself is small so a perfect reason to get delivery. Check out the extensive menu to prepare for a delicious meal!

restaurant.name: Jimbo's Hamburger Place
restaurant.description: Delicious burgers from a small New York diner that is part of New York history. Burgers are cheap and flavorful. The side dishes compliment the burgers well and will leave you wanting more.

restaurant.name: Green Cafe
restaurant.description: Gourmet cafe with fresh and savory food. Offering quick delivery makes Green Cafe easy and accessible whenever you're craving it!

restaurant.name: La Bellezza
restaurant.description: Noted for their scrumptious chicken parmigiana hero this Italian pizzeria has become many diners top lunch pick. All the food is flavorful and fresh and definitely lives up to its raving reviews.

restaurant.name: Obao
restaurant.description: Asian fusion food that not only tastes good but is not overpriced. All the dishes are beautifully constructed and will not disappoint.

restaurant.name: Chef's Secret
restaurant.description: Thai restaurant that also has some Japanese options. Portions are very large and hearty and the prices are reasonable.

restaurant.name: Energy Kitchen
restaurant.description: Following the health food craze, Energy Kitchen serves delicious and light sandwiches, salads and smoothies. With everything under 500 calories you can enjoy a guilt free yet satisfying meal.

restaurant.name: Dakshin Glatt Kosher Indian Bistro
restaurant.description: Known as New York's first and only Glatt Kosher Indian restaurant, Dakshin Indian Bistro proudly serves authentic Indian cuisine that includes an array of traditional tandoori, chicken, lamb and vegetarian dishes.

restaurant.name: Sushi Ko (formerly Yummy Sushi)
restaurant.description: Japanese cuisine hailing from midtown east. Sushi is fresh and the other Japanese style options are equally satisfying and tasty.

restaurant.name: China Fun
restaurant.description: With a menu that includes dim sum and sushi as well as the well-known Chinese favorites, China Fun is a go-to for many when ordering take-out. Bubble tea and smoothies like the Strawberry Shortcake or the White Russian are a perfect way to add some sweetness to your day!

restaurant.name: C'est Bon Cafe
restaurant.description: Refreshing deli fare that is sure to perk up any day. Sandwiches are freshly made and constructed of the best ingredients. Pizza is also made fresh from the wood oven, always piping hot and delicious.

restaurant.name: Espresso's Caffe Ristorante Italiano
restaurant.description: Espresso's Caffe promises authentic Italian dishes made with fresh ingredients daily. Take home the flavors of the Perrone & Cipriani families and have it delivered for dinner tonight!

restaurant.name: Nino's Positano
restaurant.description: Italian restaurant with delicious sizzling entrees, desert and best of all pizza. All the dishes are lip smacking good- you might want to order a variety of dishes to enjoy everything they have to offer.

restaurant.name: Hatsuhana Sushi Restaurant
restaurant.description: Great sushi restaurant with incredibly fresh fish and creative rolls. Sushi and sashimi dinners come with a lot of sushi and delicious side accompaniments.

restaurant.name: Hatsuhana Park Ave
restaurant.description: Taking the concept of fresh sushi to another level, Hatsuhana provides delicious sushi that will melt in your mouth. Other items on the menu are also a hit but nothing compares to the fresh fish dishes.

restaurant.name: Jerusalem Grill
restaurant.description: Serving Middle Eastern cuisine, Jerusalem Grill offers classics such as falafel, kebabs and stuffed grape leaves. With an extensive menu for vegetarians as well, there's something for every appetite!

restaurant.name: Il Postino
restaurant.description: Out of this world Italian cuisine that will send your taste buds and hearts to Italy. The portions are spot on, pasta cooked to a perfect al dente and the sauces are fabulous.

restaurant.name: Dawat
restaurant.description: Extensive menu that can get a bit pricey but the food is completely worth it. Indian spices and tastes transcend palates to a world of heavenly Indian cuisine.

restaurant.name: Johnny Rockets
restaurant.description: An international restaurant chain that has been around since 1986, Johnny Rockets serves fun food that has been much acclaimed for their fries and hamburgers in media. Make sure to get a milkshake to complete the experience!

restaurant.name: Fusia Asian Cuisine
restaurant.description: Asian fusion cuisine that successfully combines Thai, Vietnamese, Japanese and Chinese food. All the food is tasty and satisfying and comes with hefty portion sizes!

restaurant.name: Piada 2
restaurant.description: Diners have nothing but great things to say about Piada. A delicious Italian inspired restaurant that takes time and care into their food preparation and only use the freshest ingredients.

restaurant.name: Fresco on the Go
restaurant.description: Gourmet restaurant serving many cuisines and options for the busy New Yorker. Choices include sandwiches, wraps, paninis, burritos, grilled cheese, hot food, soup, pizza and many more.

restaurant.name: Subway Sandwich
restaurant.description: America's favorite healthy fast food joint. Nutritional subs, flatbreads and great meal combo's. Subway is always filled with plenty of choices for a delicious quick meal any time of day.

restaurant.name: Mr. K's
restaurant.description: Get a taste of extravagance when you order from Mr.K's. Chinese food. Prices can run high but the quality backs it up.

restaurant.name: Al Bustan
restaurant.description: Great spot for all your middle eastern classic and favorite dishes. The middle eastern flavors and spices are found in every dish, even when its unexpected. Great for getting a lot of appetizers and entrees and sharing with a group.

restaurant.name: A+ Thai
restaurant.description: With so many Thai restaurants in Manhattan sometimes it is hard to distinguish yourself among the rest. A+ Thai really does accomplish this with spot-on Thai dishes as well as one-of-a-kind flavors.

restaurant.name: China Moon
restaurant.description: Asian-fusion restaurant serving authentic Chinese and Thai cuisine, and conveniently located close to Rockefeller Center and Fifth Avenue.

restaurant.name: Sutton Wine Shop
restaurant.description: Excellent service and a knowledgeable staff that genuinely cares about their customers make up Sutton Wine Shop. The selection of wine is very extensive and the prices are reasonable considering the location and merchandise.

restaurant.name: Pinkberry
restaurant.description: All Pinkberrys great tasting products are made fresh with the highest quality ingredients and Pinkberrys signature tang. Our menu includes Original, Pomegranate, Chocolate, Mango, Coconut and Green Tea frozen yogurts*, daily cut fresh fruit and seasonal fresh fruit toppings, as well as creative and premium dry and liquid toppings. Pinkberry also now serves a Fresh Fruit Parfait in addition to our Original and Green Tea smoothies. Get your taste of Swirly Goodness.*Product offerings may vary by stores. Orders may take 30-45 minutes for delivery. Pinkberry Gift Cards cannot be used for Delivery.com.

restaurant.name: Calista Superfoods
restaurant.description: A healthy restaurant that serves sandwiches, wraps and other entrees. Everything is homemade daily, even the sauces and dressings!

restaurant.name: Habana Room
restaurant.description: Habana Room offers a tropical atmosphere, live music, and unparalleled Nuevo Latino cuisine.

restaurant.name: Manhattan Wine Xchange Gift Baskets
restaurant.description: If sending to a recipient other than yourself, put the GIFT BASKET RECIPIENT'S address in the SPECIAL INSTRUCTION BOX upon checkout Orders are shipped by UPS for delivery between 9am-7pm Place orders by 2pm for next day delivery Cancellations - please notify before 4pm (orders ship at 5) Manhattan Wine Xchange offers the most user-friendly, ultra-customizable service for your gift-giving needs. We have a personalized wine gift basket for every budget and every type of recipient.

Sensebowl
restaurant.description: Sensebowl was created form the desire to share modern Asian cuisine that is affordable, fast and delicious. Made to your specifications in five easy steps, Sensebowl is a smart choice for people on the go who want to eat well. Our passion is evident in the meticulous preparation of our food and the selection of the finest ingredients and highest quality proteins.Our head chef, Beena Yu, studied at the Culinary Institute of America and spent her career working at fine-dining establishments such as Bouley and Jean-Georges. Chef Yus culinary influences are evident throughout the Sensebowl menu from the rich proteins to the bold flavor combinations of their sauces. Fanatical about taste and quality, Chef Yu and her team prepare all of our food from scratch each day- from chopping the vegetables to mixing the sauces. They get to work early every morning, carefully preparing each item, ensuring that the food is free of any additives or preservatives.

restaurant.name: Fuji Sushi
restaurant.description: Fuji Sushi features a wide variety of Japanese and Chinese cuisines. This restaurant is a staple in the Midtown West area.

restaurant.name: Rising Dragon
restaurant.description: This typical Chinese restaurant offers all of your favorite dishes and entrees.

restaurant.name: BBQ Pit (brought to you by Kool Bloo)
Kool Bloo
restaurant.description: Offering healthy and non-healthy options 24/7, this eatery features typical American fare. No matter what you are in the mood for, Kool Bloo has something for you.

restaurant.name: Hiroshi Japanese Fusion
restaurant.description: Sushi that diners claim is "Oh-My-God" good. Everything is fresh and the specialty rolls have some very unique and interesting combinations.

restaurant.name: City Harvest
restaurant.description:
Make a donation to City Harvest with a Delivery.com order! You can help those in need by choosing items from the City Harvest menu. The total cost of your order will be sent as a donation to City Harvest, and help in their efforts to feed NYC's hungry. Upon receipt of your donation, you will be sent an acknowledgment letter from City Harvest.
City Harvest, the world's first and New York City's only food rescue organization, connects good food that would otherwise go to waste with people struggling with hunger. This year they will rescue 28 million pounds of food, helping to feed more than 300,000 men, women and children each week.This order will go directly to City Harvest as a monetary donation. No food will be delivered to you.

restaurant.name: Liebe
restaurant.description: At Liebe the traditional Kati Roll is reincarnated as the Liebe Roll," wrapped with the freshest local ingredients and fused with aromatic spices. All menu items are prepared daily and made to order creating a healthy, fresh-tasting experience.

restaurant.name: New York's Delicious Pizza
restaurant.description: The name says it all folks- this really is New York delicious pizza. Try any of the delicious regular cheese slices or add your toppings of choice. Whatever you choose you won't choose wrong.

restaurant.name: Chirping Chicken
restaurant.description: The name says Chirping Chicken, but there's more to this menu than just poultry. Hot pita bread and salsa are included with your meal of baby back ribs, steak, seafood, salad (and of course, chicken). The salsa is a favorite among customers, so you might want to ask for extra!

restaurant.name: Green Cafe
restaurant.description: At Green Cafe there really is something for everyone to enjoy. Menu options range from sandwiches and wraps to salads and paninis.

restaurant.name: ACI
restaurant.description: Delicious Chinese eats that can be served mild or hot. Plenty of beef, poultry and vegetarian options to satisfy all.

restaurant.name: Curry & Curry
restaurant.description: Spicy and flavorful Indian cuisine is found at Curry and Curry. Traditional and authentic dishes that have customers continually raving and returning.Available all day -$12.95 Prix Fixe Meal- Includes appetizer, entree, rice and bread.

restaurant.name: East Pacific
restaurant.description: Pan-Asian food that actually gets it right. The sushi is mouthwatering and fresh. Every dish is packed with flavor and will not disappoint.

restaurant.name: PJ Bernstein Deli-Restaurant
restaurant.description: PJ Bernstein Deli is the time-trusted eatery for classic American dishes. With options like hearty omelettes for breakfast and old fashioned beef stew for dinner, you'll be sure to eat your fill!

restaurant.name: Yatra Indian Cuisine
restaurant.description: Indian food that is so delicious it is almost indescribable. All the classic bold Indian flavors mesh so well together creating an exciting and delectable menu.

restaurant.name: Mee Summer Palace
restaurant.description: Chinese restaurant where the food is hot and tasty. Many delicious noodle options that are perfect for lunch or dinner.

restaurant.name: Ginza
restaurant.description: Japanese cuisine that is affordable, fast and delicious. Great sushi and other dishes as well- Ginza stretches your dollar as far as it will go.

restaurant.name: Royal II Thai Cuisine
restaurant.description: Royal Thai features an extensive Thai menu with many options to choose from. The restaurant is perfect for your Thai food fix.

restaurant.name: Lemongrass Grill
restaurant.description: Thai restaurant that seasons and flavors their food just right. With pad thai so delicious you won't be able to stop talking about it, Lemongrass Grill has quickly become the go to Thai spot.

restaurant.name: Nirvana Indian Restaurant
restaurant.description: Nirvana is not a place but a state of mind of peace and relaxation. This Midtown East Indian favorite will do exactly that. Always delicious the flavorful dishes can satisfy all.

restaurant.name: Bamboo Sushi
restaurant.description: Bamboo Sushi has everything you could want in a Japanese restaurant- noodles, fried rice, teriyaki, sushi and more. Order in these dishes for lunch or dinner today!

restaurant.name: Pronto Pizza
restaurant.description: This classic pizza joint has a wide variety of pizza and Italian food to choose from. Pronto Pizza is a staple in Midtown West.

restaurant.name: Carl's Steaks
restaurant.description: Authentic Philly sandwiches right here in Manhattan. The meat is always cooked fresh and seasoned with the perfect amount of salt and pepper. Nice balance of greasy deliciousness, grilled onions and quality meat.

restaurant.name: Liberty Cafe Catering
restaurant.description: If you want your favorite everyday deli food to be enjoyed by a larger crowd, Libery Cafe Catering is just the place. Assorted platters of sandwiches and deserts are available as well as some favorite taco bell dishes.

restaurant.name: Aki Sushi West
restaurant.description: Aki Sushi West is a classic sushi joint that features traditional Japanese cuisine. This Midtown West restaurant is a sushi staple in the community.

restaurant.name: Golden City
restaurant.description: Chinese food restaurant serving all the favorite classics at unbeatable prices. Chef specialties include some authentic dishes while other Chinese-American dishes are also a hit.

restaurant.name: Amber
restaurant.description: Amber proves time and time again to be a sushi lover's dream. Fresh rolls with ingredients that will melt in your mouth.

restaurant.name: Best Wingers
restaurant.description: Large wings, large portions and plenty of sauces to chose from. Wings and fried chicken that are delicious and low in price.PLEASE NOTE: Any deliveries to be made on Super Bowl Sunday, 2/6/2011, must be placed in advance. No online orders will be accepted the day of the game. Any deliveries to be made on that date have a $20 minimum and must be for Buffalo Wings, Chicken Tenders, and Buffalo Chicken Tenders only!

restaurant.name: Nana Sushi
restaurant.description: A trendy sushi spot with surprisingly low prices. Creative sushi combinations along with many delicious hot and cold appetizers make Nana Sushi a favorite for many.

restaurant.name: Papa John's Pizza
restaurant.description: Everyone's favorite pizza chain. Offering delicious specialty pizza's, one-of-a-kind crusts and side dishes that always leave customers wanting more.Regarding credit card orders: In order to process your credit card, Papa John's Pizza requires that you provide your CVV code printed on the back of your credit card. The restaurant will be contacting you after you place your order to obtain this information.

restaurant.name: Wasabi Lobby
restaurant.description: Wasabi Lobby is an Asian fusion restaurant specializing in all things creative and innovative when it comes to sushi rolls. Accompany your meal with a drink from Wasabi Lobby's selection of sake, beer, or wine!

restaurant.name: Olympic Pita
restaurant.description: Olympic Pita is a Midtown West kosher staple. The restaurant serves many Israeli and Middle Eastern dishes as well as sushi platters under strict kosher supervision.
restaurant.cuisines: Glatt Kosher, Kosher, OU Kosher, Israeli

restaurant.name: Salaam Bombay
restaurant.description: Prepared fresh to order, this Indian restaurant has a large menu of refined Indian cuisineNo deliveries north of Houston Street. Please allow up to 45 minutes for delivery.
restaurant.landmark: Between Duane Street to Reade Street

restaurant.name: Ginger Asian Fusion Catering
restaurant.description: Similar to the restaurants daily food, Ginger's catering menu is well-priced and full of delicious options. Great way to enjoy Japanese cuisine with a lot of people without breaking the bank!

restaurant.name: Aki Sushi & Grill
restaurant.description: Japanese cuisine that is fresh and satisfying. Many choose this among others because the food is consistently delicious and the sushi rolls are hearty and bigger then most places.

restaurant.name: 2nd Ave Deli
restaurant.description: A classic New York deli that gives Kosher food justice. Traditional kosher fare that could rival any Jewish grandmother's home cooked goods as well as other more modern food means that no matter how you order, you will fall in love with 2nd Ave Deli.

restaurant.name: Wine Therapy
